Right now the frontend mode management works in theory but is flimsy in practice. (mainly the boundary between tutorial and tutorial create thoughts...)

The goal is to make the whole workflow of mode/focus switching standardized and easy to reason about.

Even if in the end it is gonna be a bunch of ifs asking about current state...

Update: I think I got it.
Basically this:
interface StateContract {
	grafikaSettings: GrafikaSettings;
	initialize: (store, focus?: string) => void;
	hangleFocusChange: (store, focus?: string) => void;
	dispose: (store, newState?) => void;
}


Initialize will load the state, including but not limited to data, effects, interaction events subscription (node tap...) and more.

Dispose will cleanup after itself so that any state can use the graph.

handleFocusChange spawns a unicorn and the grafikaSettings stop trams in Brno when not null.
